WEBVTT

00:01.335 --> 00:04.635
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

00:17.484 --> 00:20.934
(DISTANT SIREN WAILING)

00:30.798 --> 00:32.566
MAN: Take the night off, boy.

00:32.633 --> 00:34.668
You deserve a little sleep.

00:34.735 --> 00:37.805
(DOOR SLAMMING)

00:37.872 --> 00:39.840
-NARRATOR: <i>Tom had to laugh.
-(LAUGHS)</i>

00:39.907 --> 00:41.809
<i>There were two things
</i> <i>he never got.</i>

00:41.876 --> 00:44.077
<i>Sleep...</i>

00:44.144 --> 00:45.379
<i>...and food.</i>

00:45.445 --> 00:46.495
(GASPS)

01:01.127 --> 01:05.666
(DOOR OPENING)

01:05.733 --> 01:10.338
Do you have water?

01:10.405 --> 01:14.743
NARRATOR: <i>Polly was
</i> <i>the elder statesman
</i> <i>of the dog park.</i>

01:14.809 --> 01:18.879
<i>She's been married
</i> <i>to that ball for the last
</i> <i>seven years.</i>

01:18.946 --> 01:22.416
Refreshing. Thank you.

01:22.482 --> 01:24.018
The name's Polly.

01:24.085 --> 01:26.319
My collar
was stolen in the park.

01:26.386 --> 01:30.324
Has my name on it.

01:30.391 --> 01:33.995
I think that no-good Barkley
did it.

01:34.062 --> 01:37.999
NARRATOR: <i>Barkley was
</i> <i>a bottom-dwelling Beagle
</i> <i>with behavioral problems.</i>

01:38.066 --> 01:40.701
<i>The mere mention
</i> <i>of his name sent fear
</i> <i>through animals' hearts.</i>

01:40.768 --> 01:45.718
Barkley, Barkley.
Barkley did it.

01:52.113 --> 01:53.680
NARRATOR: <i>But not Jerry.</i>

01:53.747 --> 01:55.248
<i>He laughed
</i> <i>in the face of fear.</i>

01:55.315 --> 01:57.619
(LAUGHING)

01:57.685 --> 02:02.685
What do you say, boys?
Can you help an old dog?

02:05.158 --> 02:06.208
Please.

02:14.535 --> 02:16.637
NARRATOR:
<i>Barkley's owners brought him
</i> <i>to the dog park one day</i>

02:16.703 --> 02:19.673
<i>and never picked him up.</i>

02:19.740 --> 02:24.311
POLLY: I'm coming!

02:24.377 --> 02:25.746
Did I forget the ball?

02:25.813 --> 02:28.182
I forgot the ball!

02:28.249 --> 02:33.249
I can't believe
I forgot the ball!

02:36.724 --> 02:40.027
NARRATOR: <i>Four collars
</i> <i>were stolen in a week
</i> <i>at the park.</i>

02:40.094 --> 02:42.330
<i>Everything pointed to Barkley.</i>

02:42.396 --> 02:47.101
<i>Sure as the night is long,
</i> <i>Barkley shows.</i>

02:47.168 --> 02:51.038
-(CRASHING)
-(SNARLING)

02:51.105 --> 02:56.105
<i>they'd have to go
</i> <i>deep undercover.</i>

02:57.545 --> 03:00.214
I don't like grass!
(GRUNTS)

03:00.281 --> 03:02.183
I don't like
drinking fountains!

03:02.249 --> 03:06.053
-(GRUNTING)
-(FOUNTAIN CRASHING)

03:06.120 --> 03:09.870
I don't like trash cans!

03:17.731 --> 03:20.601
(DOG BARKING)

03:20.667 --> 03:23.517
(PUPPY WHIMPERING)

03:27.041 --> 03:31.991
-(PUPPY WHIMPERING)
-(CRASHING)

03:38.819 --> 03:41.669
For heaven's sake.

03:48.429 --> 03:50.397
NARRATOR:
<i>It was decision time.</i>

03:50.464 --> 03:54.236
(CLOCK TICKING)

03:54.303 --> 03:57.072
<i>The cat and mouse detectives
</i> <i>can either deal with
</i> <i>this bad dog head on</i>

03:57.139 --> 04:01.208
<i>or grab the backpack
</i> <i>and run like
</i> <i>two chicken-bellied cowards.</i>

04:01.275 --> 04:04.846
<i>The choice was an easy one
</i> <i>for our fearless detectives.</i>

04:04.913 --> 04:09.913
You're messing with
the wrong dog, trash can!

04:11.051 --> 04:12.701
(RATTLING)

04:17.357 --> 04:19.126
(THUDDING)

04:19.193 --> 04:21.895
DOG CATCHER: <i>Well, well,
</i> <i>if it isn't Barkley.</i>

04:21.962 --> 04:24.397
<i>It's a two-for-one day.</i>

04:24.464 --> 04:27.734
(SNARLING)

04:27.801 --> 04:31.839
I'm coming for you, cans!

04:31.905 --> 04:35.176
Wait a minute.
Those aren't cans.

04:35.242 --> 04:36.977
That's a cat and a mouse!

04:37.044 --> 04:39.744
(ENGINE STARTING)

04:43.984 --> 04:46.388
NARRATOR: <i>Another case closed.</i>

04:46.455 --> 04:51.455
<i>Barkley was off the streets
</i> <i>and Polly would soon
</i> <i>have her collar back.</i>

04:52.727 --> 04:56.296
<i>Peace returns
</i> <i>to the hard boiled streets
</i> <i>of Tolucaville.</i>

04:56.363 --> 04:58.566
<i>Thanks to...</i>

04:58.633 --> 05:03.633
<i>...the cat and mouse
</i> <i>detectives!</i>

05:04.505 --> 05:07.174
<i>There's only one problem.</i>

05:07.241 --> 05:11.945
<i>This isn't
</i> <i>the end of the story.</i>

05:12.012 --> 05:17.012
<i>Barkley was coming
</i> <i>for revenge.</i>

05:18.119 --> 05:21.688
-GUARD: We got a runner.
Stop where you are!
-(SIRENS WAILING)

05:21.755 --> 05:25.125
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

05:25.192 --> 05:28.342
Darn electric fences.

05:40.807 --> 05:42.009
(SNORING)

05:42.076 --> 05:44.926
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

05:48.682 --> 05:51.418
(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

05:51.484 --> 05:53.420
(SCREAMING)

05:53.486 --> 05:55.736
(ALL SCREAMING)

05:59.126 --> 06:02.495
(ALL SCREAMING)

06:02.562 --> 06:04.198
Knock it off.

06:04.265 --> 06:07.801
Why are you guys
acting so nutty?

06:07.868 --> 06:10.404
I need some help.

06:10.471 --> 06:13.474
I'm looking for
a cat and mouse.

06:13.541 --> 06:17.644
Only I don't know who they are
'cause they were wearing cans.

06:17.711 --> 06:20.914
They stole my backpack.

06:20.981 --> 06:22.749
Oh, when we find them,

06:22.816 --> 06:26.753
I'm gonna rip them
limb from limb.

06:26.820 --> 06:29.820
You helping or not?

06:32.326 --> 06:35.796
The cat and mouse's address?

06:35.862 --> 06:39.500
You guys are good.

06:39.567 --> 06:44.517
I'm gonna rip 'em
limb from limb.

06:45.873 --> 06:50.745
You helping or not?

06:50.812 --> 06:55.812
You're telling me
the cat and mouse live here?

06:56.050 --> 07:01.050
I don't know, boys,
something smells fishy.

07:01.621 --> 07:03.224
(FLIES BUZZING)

07:03.290 --> 07:05.125
BARKLEY: Oh, right.
That's probably it.

07:05.192 --> 07:08.162
Let's go pay that
cat and mouse a little visit.

07:08.229 --> 07:12.666
And when I see them,
I'm gonna...

07:12.733 --> 07:14.768
(TEETH CHATTERING)

07:14.835 --> 07:16.935
Hold on, bub.

07:23.778 --> 07:27.748
Either you got a twin in there
or you took my backpack.

07:27.814 --> 07:29.314
(SQUEALS)

07:33.220 --> 07:37.057
-I'm gonna rip you...
-(CRASHING)

07:37.124 --> 07:41.661
(GROWLING)

07:41.728 --> 07:43.678
(SCREECHING)

07:46.900 --> 07:50.050
Darn electric fences.

07:54.074 --> 07:55.943
(DOGS GROWLING)

07:56.009 --> 07:58.109
(CATS MEOWING)

08:06.687 --> 08:10.857
Don't let the small legs
fool you.

08:10.924 --> 08:13.627
(WHIRRING)

08:13.693 --> 08:15.095
I'm gonna rip you...

08:15.162 --> 08:18.012
(TEETH CHATTERING)

08:23.737 --> 08:25.772
(LOUD CRASH)

08:25.839 --> 08:27.789
(SCREECHING)

08:40.521 --> 08:42.490
GUARD:
Hey, look who's back.

08:42.556 --> 08:44.625
-It's Barkley.
-(LAUGHING)

08:44.692 --> 08:46.660
-Couple of strays, eh?
-(SHRIEKING)

08:46.726 --> 08:47.961
We got laws, you know.

08:48.028 --> 08:49.997
(GATES SLAMMING SHUT)

08:50.063 --> 08:51.832
BARKLEY: Ding dong.

08:51.898 --> 08:54.802
(CLEARS THROAT) Hiya, boys.

08:54.869 --> 08:57.971
NARRATOR:
At least they weren't in
the same cage.

08:58.038 --> 09:01.038
(BLOWING RASPBERRY)

09:04.711 --> 09:06.061
(CRYING)

09:10.985 --> 09:14.054
-I'm gonna rip you...
-(PUPPY BARKING)

09:14.121 --> 09:17.090
(BARKING)

09:17.157 --> 09:19.257
(DOGS BARKING)

09:22.864 --> 09:25.967
I don't like
little yappy dogs!

09:26.034 --> 09:30.804
-(GATE OPENING)
-Well, we don't
like you either.

09:30.871 --> 09:34.475
Drop them, Barkley.

09:34.542 --> 09:37.611
-(CRASHING)
-(LAUGHING) Bring it.

09:37.678 --> 09:42.050
Back off, boys. I got this.

09:42.116 --> 09:45.553
NARRATOR: <i>She may be old and
</i> <i>lacking fur in critical places</i>

09:45.619 --> 09:50.357
<i>but she was determined not to
</i> <i>take his guff anymore.</i>

09:50.424 --> 09:55.424
<i>This was gonna get ugly fast.</i>

10:01.235 --> 10:03.770
(DOGS STOP BARKING)

10:03.837 --> 10:05.637
(SQUEAKING)

10:10.845 --> 10:15.583
NARRATOR: <i>It's not how
</i> <i>Tom and Jerry
</i> <i>would have done it.</i>

10:15.650 --> 10:17.551
WOMAN:
Polly, how did you get here?

10:17.618 --> 10:21.955
Girl, come to Mama.

10:22.022 --> 10:26.672
Did you make a new friend, eh?

10:28.096 --> 10:31.365
NARRATOR:
<i>Maybe, Tom and Jerry could get
</i> <i>some much need sleep now.</i>

10:31.432 --> 10:34.468
<i>Harmony was once again
</i> <i>returned to the city</i>

10:34.535 --> 10:37.471
<i>and a hardened criminal
</i> <i>got a second chance.</i>

10:37.538 --> 10:40.707
<i>Thanks to
</i> <i>the cat and mouse detectives.</i>
